Field Detail

SEPERATOR

static final java.lang.String SEPERATOR
This is a string separator is in between two separate entries for the input files. For consistency you must also insert this separator in between different entries for the output file. The exact layout of your output file will be described in the project write up.

See Also:

Method Detail

readInput

void readInput(java.lang.String birdName,
               java.lang.String inputFile)
               throws java.io.IOException,
                      InvalidDataException
This method reads a file with file name: inputFile associated with birdName and parses all of the data in the file and stores it in 4 different LinkedLists. The program must keep track of these lists internally as an external could request access to these data structures via getter methods.

Parameters:
- - birdName the name of the bird the program is currently reading.
- - inputFile the name of the file to read the input data from. The file should be in current directory or specify a full path.
Throws:
- - IOException if any File IO operations fail
- - InvalidDataException if any data set does not conform to the specified formats
java.io.IOException
InvalidDataException
